The latest version of the Directory Services stuff is dated September 86
(Egham).   You should be able to get this from ANSI, as it is now
at DP (Draft Proposal) status.   There will be further updates in
March (Munich) and June (Tokyo).    November 87 is a rigid deadline,
as this is the latest date for being able to be issued as a 1988
CCITT standard (CCITT and ISO are now working jointly on Directory
Services).

Progress: some of the previous problems have now been resolved.
The information framework seems to  be stabilising (apart from a
new concept called 'attribute inheritance').  However, the
distributed operations section still has an awful long way to go.
I think you would need to be optimistic to believe that there
are now less open questions thatn there were 6 months back.

Steve

